A technical property generally refers to a characteristic or attribute that defines or describes the technical aspects of an object, system, material, or process. The switching function of the magnetic sensor is the way the sensor changes its state in response to a change in the magnetic field. It can be a NO (Normally Open) or NC (Normally Closed) contact, or a REED contact, which is a type of magnetic switch used for switching electrical circuits.
